    <p>SmartSweets disrupted the candy industry by proving that low-sugar gummies could taste genuinely good. Founded in 2016 by Tara Bosch in Vancouver, the brand reformulated the traditional gummy bear by replacing sugar with allulose (a rare sugar with 70% the sweetness of sucrose but only 0.2-0.4 calories per gram) and stevia leaf extract. The pectin-and-fiber base delivers a satisfying chew without gelatin, while 28g of soluble corn fiber per bag provides prebiotic benefits that feed beneficial gut bacteria. The tradeoff is a slightly firmer, less bouncy texture compared to full-sugar pectin gummies — but for consumers managing sugar intake, SmartSweets is the clear category leader.</p>

